reviews.text: Average station. If you're crossing the road either by car or foot you'll be waiting for a few days. Bite the bullet and walk the bridge....

The ladies in the booking office were GREAT today. Giving advice and helping me to continue my journey to Ipswich.
More "blond assistance executives" should be installed. 
I do apologise I never took the blond ladies name.

Just a small and average station on the far zones of the oyster boundary. Served by Overground services every 30 minutes here but don't be surprised if there is disruption from this station due to the constraints of the main line.
Rude staff. Reluctant to open gate for you
Small station, crowded car park - usually with minicabs. Good access to London. Oyster works from here. Great for access to Lee Valley Park, only a short walk away.
